%YAML 1.1
%TAG !u! tag:unity3d.com,2011:
--- !u!114 &11400000
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 8ef4a382a350f98438c21cfd3c789fdf, type: 3}
  m_Name: Liberties
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  lessonTitle: Liberties
  lessonId: liberties
  slides:
  - slideName: Slide 1
    slideType: 0
    bodyText: Of course, stones placed on the board aren't immortal. They all have
      "liberties". If a stone or a group of stones runs out of liberties, they are
      captured, or taken off the board.
    boardSource: 1
    boardJsonFile: {fileID: 4900000, guid: cbf5d3bbfcdfe9d41bd8da8451bde56e, type: 3}
    inlineBoardSize: 9
    inlineCurrentPlayer: 2
    inlineBoardFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationTypeFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationNumberFlat: 
    correctYesAnswer: 1
    correctNumberAnswer: 0
  - slideName: Slide 2
    slideType: 0
    bodyText: Liberties are empty intersections orthogonally (that is, intersections
      to the left, right, up, or down of the stone, not diagonal) next to stones.
      For example, this stone has 4 liberties as shown.
    boardSource: 1
    boardJsonFile: {fileID: 4900000, guid: 979bfac1bf749ec49ac8bc33efe20e20, type: 3}
    inlineBoardSize: 9
    inlineCurrentPlayer: 2
    inlineBoardFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationTypeFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationNumberFlat: 
    correctYesAnswer: 1
    correctNumberAnswer: 0
  - slideName: Slide 3
    slideType: 0
    bodyText: When there are stones orthogonally next to a stone of the same color,
      they are considered one group of stones and share liberties. The two black
      stones on the right count as a group and has 6 liberties.
    boardSource: 1
    boardJsonFile: {fileID: 4900000, guid: 037900f09e92adf41993130ad7782f96, type: 3}
    inlineBoardSize: 9
    inlineCurrentPlayer: 1
    inlineBoardFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationTypeFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationNumberFlat: 
    correctYesAnswer: 1
    correctNumberAnswer: 0
  - slideName: Slide 3
    slideType: 0
    bodyText: ' However, the two white stones on the left are not a group due to
      not being orthogonally connected.'
    boardSource: 1
    boardJsonFile: {fileID: 4900000, guid: 037900f09e92adf41993130ad7782f96, type: 3}
    inlineBoardSize: 9
    inlineCurrentPlayer: 1
    inlineBoardFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationTypeFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationNumberFlat: 
    correctYesAnswer: 1
    correctNumberAnswer: 0
  - slideName: Slide 4
    slideType: 2
    bodyText: Comprehension check. Are these white stones one group?
    boardSource: 0
    boardJsonFile: {fileID: 4900000, guid: 176631b323471aa48a0c9bd7d19918b3, type: 3}
    inlineBoardSize: 9
    inlineCurrentPlayer: 1
    inlineBoardFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationTypeFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationNumberFlat: 
    correctYesAnswer: 1
    correctNumberAnswer: 0
  - slideName: Slide 5
    slideType: 3
    bodyText: Correct! Now, how many liberties does it have?
    boardSource: 0
    boardJsonFile: {fileID: 4900000, guid: 176631b323471aa48a0c9bd7d19918b3, type: 3}
    inlineBoardSize: 9
    inlineCurrentPlayer: 1
    inlineBoardFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationTypeFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationNumberFlat: 
    correctYesAnswer: 1
    correctNumberAnswer: 10
  - slideName: Slide 5
    slideType: 0
    bodyText: Correct again! That was a tough one.
    boardSource: 1
    boardJsonFile: {fileID: 4900000, guid: 176631b323471aa48a0c9bd7d19918b3, type: 3}
    inlineBoardSize: 9
    inlineCurrentPlayer: 1
    inlineBoardFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationTypeFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationNumberFlat: 
    correctYesAnswer: 1
    correctNumberAnswer: 10
  - slideName: Slide 6
    slideType: 2
    bodyText: Are these black stones one group?
    boardSource: 0
    boardJsonFile: {fileID: 4900000, guid: ca63c22c5b1b0304688c8d3f61ad0b52, type: 3}
    inlineBoardSize: 9
    inlineCurrentPlayer: 1
    inlineBoardFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationTypeFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationNumberFlat: 
    correctYesAnswer: 0
    correctNumberAnswer: 0
  - slideName: Slide 7
    slideType: 0
    bodyText: Precisely. Notice how they are not connected orthogonally. Remember
      diagonals doesn't count.
    boardSource: 0
    boardJsonFile: {fileID: 4900000, guid: ca63c22c5b1b0304688c8d3f61ad0b52, type: 3}
    inlineBoardSize: 9
    inlineCurrentPlayer: 1
    inlineBoardFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationTypeFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationNumberFlat: 
    correctYesAnswer: 1
    correctNumberAnswer: 0
  - slideName: Slide 8
    slideType: 0
    bodyText: There are no liberties outside the edges. There is also no liberty
      on an intersection that is taken by an opponent's stone.
    boardSource: 0
    boardJsonFile: {fileID: 4900000, guid: 3888354209bebb644919fe3bcb777b24, type: 3}
    inlineBoardSize: 9
    inlineCurrentPlayer: 1
    inlineBoardFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationTypeFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationNumberFlat: 
    correctYesAnswer: 1
    correctNumberAnswer: 0
  - slideName: Slide 9
    slideType: 0
    bodyText: For example, examine this group of black stones. It has 11 liberties.
    boardSource: 1
    boardJsonFile: {fileID: 4900000, guid: 99b7bdbd566e3b846acb33598c61ccf1, type: 3}
    inlineBoardSize: 9
    inlineCurrentPlayer: 1
    inlineBoardFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationTypeFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationNumberFlat: 
    correctYesAnswer: 1
    correctNumberAnswer: 0
  - slideName: Slide 10
    slideType: 0
    bodyText: Here is the same group but next to the edge. Due to there being no
      liberties outside the edge, it now only has 5.
    boardSource: 1
    boardJsonFile: {fileID: 4900000, guid: c74c29b7281319943aa5799397a2c37f, type: 3}
    inlineBoardSize: 9
    inlineCurrentPlayer: 1
    inlineBoardFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationTypeFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationNumberFlat: 
    correctYesAnswer: 1
    correctNumberAnswer: 0
  - slideName: Slide 11
    slideType: 0
    bodyText: White went ahead and took some more of it's liberties. Now it only
      has 2. How unfortunate.
    boardSource: 1
    boardJsonFile: {fileID: 4900000, guid: d72510c54735e654994028727adfd4c1, type: 3}
    inlineBoardSize: 9
    inlineCurrentPlayer: 1
    inlineBoardFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationTypeFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationNumberFlat: 
    correctYesAnswer: 1
    correctNumberAnswer: 0
  - slideName: Slide 12
    slideType: 3
    bodyText: Now it's your turn. How many liberties does this group of black stones
      have?
    boardSource: 0
    boardJsonFile: {fileID: 4900000, guid: f5d4f1a1f5da4fc489803b895e73807d, type: 3}
    inlineBoardSize: 9
    inlineCurrentPlayer: 1
    inlineBoardFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationTypeFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationNumberFlat: 
    correctYesAnswer: 1
    correctNumberAnswer: 6
  - slideName: Slide 13
    slideType: 3
    bodyText: How many liberties does this group of white stones have? Careful, this
      one might be a bit tricky.
    boardSource: 0
    boardJsonFile: {fileID: 4900000, guid: 3dc4021d931e5424b98813386b746cdf, type: 3}
    inlineBoardSize: 9
    inlineCurrentPlayer: 1
    inlineBoardFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationTypeFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationNumberFlat: 
    correctYesAnswer: 1
    correctNumberAnswer: 5
  - slideName: Slide 14
    slideType: 0
    bodyText: Nicely done. Now that you know how liberties work, try capturing white's
      stones as black by depleting its liberties.
    boardSource: 0
    boardJsonFile: {fileID: 4900000, guid: 3888354209bebb644919fe3bcb777b24, type: 3}
    inlineBoardSize: 9
    inlineCurrentPlayer: 1
    inlineBoardFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationTypeFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationNumberFlat: 
    correctYesAnswer: 1
    correctNumberAnswer: 0
  - slideName: Slide 15
    slideType: 1
    bodyText: Capture this white stone!
    boardSource: 0
    boardJsonFile: {fileID: 4900000, guid: 2b3353954f1fa544396e5bba12338451, type: 3}
    inlineBoardSize: 9
    inlineCurrentPlayer: 1
    inlineBoardFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationTypeFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationNumberFlat: 
    correctYesAnswer: 1
    correctNumberAnswer: 0
  - slideName: Slide 16
    slideType: 1
    bodyText: This group next!
    boardSource: 0
    boardJsonFile: {fileID: 4900000, guid: dacb7d09b68d8b74db9ee1a6b00a89d6, type: 3}
    inlineBoardSize: 9
    inlineCurrentPlayer: 1
    inlineBoardFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationTypeFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationNumberFlat: 
    correctYesAnswer: 1
    correctNumberAnswer: 0
  - slideName: Slide 17
    slideType: 1
    bodyText: Final test. White may try to escape this one!
    boardSource: 0
    boardJsonFile: {fileID: 4900000, guid: dc545a2e60329bb4a845c58daf2afd8f, type: 3}
    inlineBoardSize: 9
    inlineCurrentPlayer: 1
    inlineBoardFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationTypeFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationNumberFlat: 
    correctYesAnswer: 1
    correctNumberAnswer: 0
  - slideName: Slide 18
    slideType: 0
    bodyText: Congrats! You have mastered how liberties work and basic capturing.
      See you in the next one!
    boardSource: 0
    boardJsonFile: {fileID: 4900000, guid: 3888354209bebb644919fe3bcb777b24, type: 3}
    inlineBoardSize: 9
    inlineCurrentPlayer: 1
    inlineBoardFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationTypeFlat: 
    inlineAnnotationNumberFlat: 
    correctYesAnswer: 1
    correctNumberAnswer: 0
